### Description

Looks like Angular version 18.2.14 has a bug on @Directive standalone compiling

the directive:

```
import { Directive, ElementRef, HostListener } from '@angular/core';
@Directive({
  selector: '[appHighlight]',
  standalone: true
})
export class HighlightDirective {
  constructor(private el: ElementRef) { }
  @HostListener('mouseenter') onMouseEnter(): void {
    this.highlight('yellow');
  }
  @HostListener('mouseleave') onMouseLeave(): void {
    this.highlight('');
  }
  private highlight(color: string): void {
    this.el.nativeElement.style.backgroundColor = color;
  }
}
```
I have a page which used it
```
  <div >
    <h1>Hello, {{ title }}</h1>
    <p appHighlight>Congratulations! Your app is running. </p>
  </div>
```
So I need to add them into imports like this:
```
  standalone: true,
  imports: [RouterOutlet, HighlightDirective, IfNullPipe],
```
But compiling didn’t complain if I remove it from imports and the page function is silently broken

I tried to remove other necessary components like IfNullPipe and immediately get compiling error

I knew in HTML spec, an element can add any extra attribute 

But  I still think it is a bug on @Directive standalone compiling because its silent failure make it dangerous

