### Description

When doing the Angular 21 migration (coming from Angular 20), the `@angular/material` package was also bumped from `20.2.9` to `21.0.6`. After the migrations, we've noticed odd behaviour concerning the flyout of the Material Autocomplete. On the first input/results, the flyout shifts to the top of the page. When input is added, the next options are shown in the correct position.

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/de9f13b8-87e7-4418-80df-f94f9b591376)

We can only reproduce this bug in Chrome. No issues in Firefox. I've gone down one version at a time to `21.0.0`. It only disappears when I hit `20.2.9`.

### Reproduction

I'm under a deadline atm. for a production release. If this issue can't be tackled without a reproduction, I will add one in the coming week when I have time.

As an indication, this is our autocomplete component:
```html
